        "text": [
            "श्रद्धया परया तप्तं तपस्तत्त्रिविधं नरै: ।",
            "अफलाकाङ्‌क्षिभिर्युक्तै: सात्त्विकं परिचक्षते ॥ १७ ॥"
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "textGroup",
        "groupStyle": [
            "mb-5"
        ],
        "textStyle": [
            "has-text-centered",
            "is-italic",
            "mb-1"
        ],
        "text": [
            "śraddhayā parayā taptaṁ",
            "tapas tat tri-vidhaṁ naraiḥ",
            "aphalākāṅkṣibhir yuktaiḥ",
            "sāttvikaṁ paricakṣate"
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "textGroup",
        "groupStyle": [
            "mb-3"
        ],
        "textStyle": [
            "has-text-centered",
            "has-text-weight-bold"
        ],
        "text": [
            "Synonyms"
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "textGroup",
        "groupStyle": [
            "mb-5"
        ],
        "textStyle": [
            "has-text-justified"
        ],
        "text": [
            "**śraddhayā** — with faith; **parayā** — transcendental; **taptam** — executed; **tapaḥ** — austerity; **tat** — that; **tri**-**vidham** — of three kinds; **naraiḥ** — by men; **aphala**-**ākāṅkṣibhiḥ** — who are without desires for fruits; **yuktaiḥ** — engaged; **sāttvikam** — in the mode of goodness; **paricakṣate** — is called."
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "textGroup",
        "groupStyle": [
            "mb-3"
        ],
        "textStyle": [
            "has-text-centered",
            "has-text-weight-bold"
        ],
        "text": [
            "Translation"
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "textGroup",
        "groupStyle": [
            "mb-5"
        ],
        "textStyle": [
            "has-text-justified"
        ],
        "text": [
            "This threefold austerity, performed with transcendental faith by men not expecting material benefits but engaged only for the sake of the Supreme, is called austerity in goodness."
        ]
    }
]